The paper discusses the development of OpenJML, a tool for software verification of Java programs using JML, OpenJDK, and Eclipse. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it involves the development of a tool for software development. The paper also mentions the use of formal methods and specification languages (cs.PL) in the verification process. Additionally, the paper discusses the automation of tasks (cs.LO) and experimentation with different techniques (cs.FL) in software verification.
